Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

8:45 AM Defendant Santana C Jackson in court, in custody.  Attorney Kara M Rolf in court for Santana C Jackson.  Attorney Ben Wagner Daniel R. Hess in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Leave case 21CF170 on for trial, cancel 12/2 jury status and all cases to be set for 11/17.
Jury status hearing on November 17, 2022 at 10:30 am.
Status conference on October 11, 2022 at 08:30 am.
ADA Hess, Atty Rolf and defn appeared in person. Trial dates set for case 21CF170 and all other cases to follow as status. Notice to be mailed
and notice of DNA and witness list
Copy of minutes from PH Hrg on 6/7/22 and bond form sent electronically to DCJ.

- Defendant shall not operate a motor vehicle. 
- Defendant shall not use/possess controlled substances or drug paraphernalia without a valid prescription.

Information was E-filed with the court and a copy was given to the defendant; Defendant waived reading of Information; Defendant stood mute, Court enters plea of Not Guilty; motions due in 20 days; bail continued.

09:59 AM Defendant in court, in custody with Attorney Kara M Rolf with intern Peter Rakke.  Rebekah M Rennicke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State requests cts 1,2 be found transactionally related, DE does not object. Court finds cts 1,2 transactionally related. Officer T. Runkle duly sworn, direct and cross. Officer identified Defn in court. State moves for bind over, waives argument and reserves rebuttal. DE objects, waives argument. Court finds PC, case bound over for trial. On the motion for BBH: state objects, gives argument. Argument from Atty Rolf to $750. Court makes findings, orders bail modified as follows: Cash reduced to $1250 ALL NON MONITARY CONDITIONS REMAIN THE SAME.
